# Figma to Code Conversion

## Conversion Workflow

### Step 1: Component Analysis
1. Identify the component type (Button, Card, Form, Layout, etc.)
2. Determine if it's a new component or modification of existing
3. Check for reusable sub-components
4. Note any state requirements (use Zustand if global, useState if local)

### Step 2: Structure Planning
1. Create component file: `src/components/ComponentName.tsx`
2. Define TypeScript interface for props: `ComponentNameProps`
3. Plan component hierarchy (parent/child relationships)
4. Identify which parts need to be extracted into separate components

### Step 3: Layout Implementation
1. Start with container structure (div, section, article, etc.)
2. Use Tailwind flexbox/grid utilities for layout:
   - `flex`, `flex-col`, `flex-row`
   - `grid`, `grid-cols-{n}`
   - `items-center`, `justify-between`, etc.
3. Apply spacing: `p-{n}`, `m-{n}`, `gap-{n}`
4. Set dimensions: `w-{n}`, `h-{n}`, `max-w-{n}`

### Step 4: Typography
1. Apply font sizes: `text-xs` through `text-6xl`
2. Set font weights: `font-normal`, `font-medium`, `font-semibold`, `font-bold`
3. Apply text colors: `text-gray-900`, `text-blue-600`, etc.
4. Set line height if needed: `leading-tight`, `leading-normal`, `leading-relaxed`

### Step 5: Colors & Styling
1. Background colors: `bg-white`, `bg-gray-100`, `bg-blue-600`
2. Border colors: `border-gray-200`, `border-blue-500`
3. Text colors: `text-gray-900`, `text-blue-600`
4. Use semantic color names from Tailwind palette

### Step 6: Interactive Elements
1. Buttons: Use semantic HTML `<button>` with proper `onClick` handlers
2. Links: Use `<a>` or React Router `<Link>` with proper `href`
3. Forms: Use proper form elements with labels and accessibility
4. Add hover states: `hover:bg-blue-700`, `hover:shadow-lg`
5. Add focus states: `focus:outline-none`, `focus:ring-2`, `focus:ring-blue-500`
6. Add transitions: `transition-colors`, `transition-all`, `duration-200`

### Step 7: Responsive Design
1. Mobile-first approach: Base styles for mobile
2. Add breakpoint prefixes: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` for larger screens
3. Test responsive behavior: `md:flex-row`, `lg:grid-cols-3`

### Step 8: Component Props & Types
```typescript
interface ComponentNameProps {
  title: string
  description?: string
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary'
  onClick?: () => void
  className?: string
}

function ComponentName({ 
  title, 
  description, 
  variant = 'primary',
  onClick,
  className = ''
}: ComponentNameProps) {
  // implementation
}
```

### Step 9: State Management
- **Local state**: Use `useState` for component-specific state
- **Global state**: Use Zustand stores in `src/store/`
- **Form state**: Consider React Hook Form for complex forms
- **Server state**: Use appropriate data fetching library

### Step 10: Accessibility
1. Semantic HTML: Use proper elements (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, etc.)
2. ARIA labels: Add `aria-label`, `aria-describedby` when needed
3. Keyboard navigation: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
4. Focus management: Visible focus indicators
5. Alt text: For images, use descriptive `alt` attributes

### Step 11: Testing
1. Create test file: `src/components/ComponentName.test.tsx`
2. Test rendering: Component renders without errors
3. Test interactions: Click handlers, form submissions
4. Test accessibility: Screen reader compatibility
5. Test responsive: Different screen sizes

## Common Patterns

### Card Component
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 max-w-md">
  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">{title}</h3>
  <p className="text-gray-600">{description}</p>
</div>
```

### Button Variants
```tsx
const buttonStyles = {
  primary: 'bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white',
  secondary: 'bg-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-300 text-gray-900',
  outline: 'border-2 border-blue-600 text-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-50'
}

<button className={`px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-semibold transition-colors ${buttonStyles[variant]}`}>
  {children}
</button>
```

### Form Input
```tsx
<div className="mb-4">
  <label htmlFor="email" className="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
    Email
  </label>
  <input
    type="email"
    id="email"
    className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"
    placeholder="Enter your email"
  />
</div>
```

## Quality Checklist

Before considering conversion complete:
- [ ] TypeScript types defined for all props
- [ ] Tailwind classes used (no inline styles)
- [ ] Responsive design implemented
- [ ] Accessibility attributes added
- [ ] Hover/focus states implemented
- [ ] Component is reusable and well-structured
- [ ] Test file created
- [ ] Code formatted with Prettier
- [ ] Matches Figma design (pixel-perfect or close)
